replies.comment info:
@Logan 

Nice headline! Also, take a look at the Previous Month graph and compare it to the Previous Year graph when it comes to things like hobbies. What does this comparison tell us?  

Hobbies is one of seven categories which have switched direction.  What’s happening for these categories?

@Alessia 
I agree with you and how this graph shows the effects of the pandemic throughout the economy.  As you said many businesses and restaurants have closed, and they haven't gotten as much business, but try to think on the positive side.  People haven't been going as many places, meaning they are wasting less gas and that is very good for our environment.  Although it certainly has created damage to our economy, people have done more for the environment and have figured out more of what they like to enjoy.   Notice how the garden, building materials, and hobbies sections increased.  People have gotten to spend more time doing things they love and have fun with.  
There are some positives to what seem like such a negative time.
